My own sister.

1313
01:34:45,334 --> 01:34:48,462
My best friend.

1314
01:34:48,571 --> 01:34:52,268
And the worst part is,
I can't talk to anyone about it.

1315
01:34:52,374 --> 01:34:55,343
If I tell my father, he'll get
all panicked and mad at me...

1316
01:34:55,444 --> 01:34:57,912
for not taking better care of her.

1317
01:34:58,013 --> 01:35:02,575
And if I tell Simon—
I can't tell Simon.

1318
01:35:02,685 --> 01:35:04,812
Why not?

1319
01:35:04,920 --> 01:35:06,945
Because...

1320
01:35:08,791 --> 01:35:10,759
he'll hate her.

1321
01:35:12,194 --> 01:35:14,856
And that, I couldn't bear.

1322
01:35:26,942 --> 01:35:28,705
Hi, Jim.

1323
01:35:30,479 --> 01:35:34,313
Here I am, trying to be patient,
trying to be understanding...

1324
01:35:34,416 --> 01:35:36,384
while you lose your freaking mind.

1325
01:35:36,485 --> 01:35:40,114
- I'm not losing my mind.
- Ping-ponging between
comatose and homicidal.

1326
01:35:40,222 --> 01:35:44,454
God, every day I wake up thinking,
"Maybe today's the day she'll come back.

1327
01:35:44,560 --> 01:35:47,529
- I'm right here.
- "Maybe today she'll look at me like she used to.

1328
01:35:47,630 --> 01:35:51,623
She'll— She'll look at me in the eye,
tell me what she's thinking."

1329
01:35:51,734 --> 01:35:53,668
- Simon?
- But no, no, no.

1330
01:35:53,769 --> 01:35:56,203
Today's the day
you look him in the eye...

1331
01:35:56,305 --> 01:35:58,273
tell him what you're thinking.

1332
01:35:58,374 --> 01:36:03,311
The guy who treated you
like a— like a disposable washrag.

1333
01:36:28,103 --> 01:36:31,368
