1334
01:36:31,473 --> 01:36:33,634
This is about you and me—

1335
01:36:33,742 --> 01:36:39,339
you not talking to me, you not
telling me what's going on inside you.

1336
01:36:41,016 --> 01:36:43,177
Tell me.

1337
01:36:46,889 --> 01:36:50,052
[Sighs]

1338
01:36:50,159 --> 01:36:52,593
I won't marry you like this.

1339
01:36:54,463 --> 01:36:56,431
I won't do it.

1340
01:37:01,537 --> 01:37:03,471
[Car Drives Away]

1341
01:37:13,082 --> 01:37:16,950
So this lady today, she, um— she heard
about how I shopped for Mrs. Lefkowitz...

1342
01:37:17,052 --> 01:37:19,612
and she asked
if I'd do the same for her.

1343
01:37:19,722 --> 01:37:21,690
- No kidding?
- Yeah.

1344
01:37:23,158 --> 01:37:25,456
- Said she'd pay.
- Well, she'd better.

1345
01:37:32,368 --> 01:37:36,327
- Do you think there's other women
down here who would?
- Are you kidding? Scads.

1346
01:37:38,941 --> 01:37:43,173
I was thinking of doing it
maybe like... a business.

1347
01:37:46,882 --> 01:37:49,350
Well, that's an excellent idea.

1348
01:37:52,688 --> 01:37:56,454
Um, I'm really terrible at numbers.

1349
01:37:56,558 --> 01:37:58,856
I mean, adding and stuff.

1350
01:38:01,830 --> 01:38:03,957
Well, I'm good with them.
I can help.

1351
01:38:07,369 --> 01:38:09,530
I mean, if you like.

1352
01:38:12,708 --> 01:38:14,608
Yeah. Sure.

1353
01:38:20,115 --> 01:38:22,879
That'd be good.

1354
01:38:23,986 --> 01:38:25,647
Gin.

1355
01:38:48,877 --> 01:38:50,708
[Gasps]

1356
01:38:50,813 --> 01:38:52,781
[Knocking]

1357
01:38:54,683 --> 01:38:57,243
- Oh, no.
- Dad?

1358
01:38:58,454 --> 01:39:00,422
- Dad?
- You are not welcome here!

1359
01:39:00,522 --> 01:39:03,320
- Rose? You all right?
- Are you kidding?

1360
01:39:03,425 --> 01:39:07,020
I'm fantastic. Turns out I have
a grandmother I never knew about.

1361
01:39:07,129 --> 01:39:09,256
It was in your own best interest.
Your father thought—

1362
01:39:09,364 --> 01:39:12,891
Why are you speaking? You do not
have any place in this conversation.

1363
01:39:13,001 --> 01:39:17,665
- Excuse me, miss. This is my house.
- Sydelle. Please.

1364
01:39:24,947 --> 01:39:26,915
How did she find you?

1365
01:39:28,116 --> 01:39:30,812
How did she lose me?

1366
01:39:32,721 --> 01:39:35,189
She said she sent birthday cards.

1367
01:39:35,290 --> 01:39:37,656
Please tell me you never got 'em.

1368
01:39:39,394 --> 01:39:43,296
Our mother was dead,
our father was practically catatonic.

1369
01:39:43,398 --> 01:39:47,459
- A grandmother might have come in handy.
- She was impossible, Rose.

1370
01:39:47,569 --> 01:39:52,336
Bossy, self-righteous, nosy about things
that weren't her business.

1371
01:39:52,441 --> 01:39:55,501
- Like what?
- Trust me. We were better off without her.

1372
01:39:55,611 --> 01:39:57,511
Because she was bossy?
That doesn't make any sense.

1373
01:39:57,613 --> 01:40:00,309
I didn't want to be around that,
and I didn't want you around it.

1374
01:40:00,415 --> 01:40:02,315
- What?
- The judgment. The blame.

1375
01:40:02,417 --> 01:40:05,352
- For what? What-What'd she blame you for?
- Everything.

1376
01:40:05,454 --> 01:40:07,786
- What everything?
- Just everything.

1377
01:40:07,890 --> 01:40:10,620
- Dad!
- For your mother, all right?

1378
01:40:10,726 --> 01:40:12,694
For her death.

1379
01:40:16,698 --> 01:40:19,360
- She said that?
- She didn't have to.

1380
01:40:22,170 --> 01:40:26,539
She wanted her protected
all the time. Drugged.

1381
01:40:26,642 --> 01:40:29,805
But Caroline—
she didn't want to live that way.

1382
01:40:29,912 --> 01:40:32,210
It made her foggy.

1383
01:40:32,314 --> 01:40:35,078
She couldn't take it
if she was pregnant.

1384
01:40:35,183 --> 01:40:38,880
So... we hoped it would be enough—

1385
01:40:38,987 --> 01:40:42,787
loving each other,
loving you and Maggie.

1386
01:40:44,826 --> 01:40:47,454
There were so many good days.

1387
01:40:48,664 --> 01:40:51,656
We thought it would be okay.

1388
01:40:51,767 --> 01:40:54,463
Oh, God.

1389
01:40:54,570 --> 01:40:56,538
I'm sorry, Rosie.

1390
01:40:57,839 --> 01:40:59,898
I'm so sorry.

1391
01:41:00,008 --> 01:41:03,466
[Ella]
Now, um...

1392
01:41:03,579 --> 01:41:07,413
the only opening on Thursday
she has is 5:00.

1393
01:41:07,516 --> 01:41:09,416
- P.M.?
- Yes.

1394
01:41:09,518 --> 01:41:12,282
- That's right in the middle of dinner.
- Well, take it or leave it.

1395
01:41:12,387 --> 01:41:15,447
- I'll take it if she won't.
- I'll take it. I'll take it.

1396
01:41:15,557 --> 01:41:17,047
- "Mrs. Stempel."
- Ella.

1397
01:41:17,159 --> 01:41:21,061
Lewis! Are you looking
for a personal shopper too?

1398
01:41:21,163 --> 01:41:23,927
[Chuckling]
No. A date, to the Tea Dance.

1399
01:41:24,032 --> 01:41:26,830
And I'd be honored
if you'd go with me.

1400
01:41:29,538 --> 01:41:33,474
- I'd love to.
- Pick you up at 4:00.

1401
01:41:36,745 --> 01:41:40,875
- Lewis Feldman.
- Ooh.

1402
01:41:50,125 --> 01:41:53,151
This place just keeps
getting better and better.

1403
01:42:08,443 --> 01:42:10,968
[Humming]

1404
01:42:12,514 --> 01:42:14,482
[Gasps]

1405
01:42:16,618 --> 01:42:18,586
What are you doing here?

1406
01:42:21,857 --> 01:42:23,950
